<div class="postcell post-layout--right">
    
    <div class="s-prose js-post-body" itemprop="text">
                
<p>I am new to Grunt, trying to find a way to load multiple HTML files and parse them to extract some values.</p>

<p>I tried to use <code>jQuery.parseHTML</code>, <code>HTMLParser</code> but both are not defined. Is there a way to include jQuery or a lib that can parse HTML?</p>

<pre class="default s-code-block"><code data-highlighted="yes" class="hljs language-php">grunt.config.<span class="hljs-title function_ invoke__">init</span>({
    <span class="hljs-attr">concat</span>: {
        <span class="hljs-attr">options</span>: {
            <span class="hljs-attr">dest</span>: <span class="hljs-string">'tmp'</span>,
            <span class="hljs-attr">templates</span>: [<span class="hljs-string">'public/*.html'</span>]
        }
    }
});

<span class="hljs-keyword">var</span> recursiveConcat = <span class="hljs-function"><span class="hljs-keyword">function</span>(<span class="hljs-params">source, result</span>)</span>{
    grunt.file.<span class="hljs-title function_ invoke__">expand</span>(source).<span class="hljs-title function_ invoke__">forEach</span>(function(file){
        <span class="hljs-keyword">var</span> data = grunt.file.<span class="hljs-title function_ invoke__">read</span>(file);
        <span class="hljs-comment">// parse html to dom</span>
        result += data;
    });
    <span class="hljs-keyword">return</span> result;
};
</code></pre>
    </div>

