<div class="answercell post-layout--right">
    
    <div class="s-prose js-post-body" itemprop="text">
<p>It looks like writing your own Grunt Task is pretty straightforward. 
Samples and walkthroughs <a href="https://quickleft.com/blog/grunt-js-custom-tasks/" rel="nofollow">here</a> and <a href="http://javascriptplayground.com/blog/2014/01/creating-your-first-grunt-plugin/" rel="nofollow">here</a></p>

<p>then you create a task using <a href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/htmlparser" rel="nofollow">htmlparser</a> to manage your process. </p>

<p>However unless you are going to re-use this or pair it with some other grunt task (like grunt-watch) you might find it easier to just create a node script using htmlparser</p>
    </div>
